remarks: Given the exclusivities set in the hypotheses, there exist a proof where ch, th, ta, et exclude ze, si accordingly (Contributed by Jarvin Udandy, 7-Sep-2016.)
statement:
mdandyvrx11.1 $e |- ( ph \/_ ze ) $.
mdandyvrx11.2 $e |- ( ps \/_ si ) $.
mdandyvrx11.3 $e |- ( ch <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvrx11.4 $e |- ( th <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvrx11.5 $e |- ( ta <-> ph ) $.
mdandyvrx11.6 $e |- ( et <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvrx11 $p |- ( ( ( ( ch \/_ si ) /\ ( th \/_ si ) ) /\ ( ta \/_ ze ) ) /\ ( et \/_ si ) ) $.
